          <type>int</type>
          <declname>index</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Set the depth index of this visual. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Depth-index controls draw-order for overlapping visuals. Visuals with higher depth indices are rendered in front of other visual with smaller values.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>The value of index will be clamped between <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DepthIndex_1a69e209901b5045f9943328fbb8989144a7930705e7d4fa160d2051c990c025f11" kindref="member">DepthIndex::Ranges::MINIMUM_DEPTH_INDEX</ref> and <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DepthIndex_1a69e209901b5045f9943328fbb8989144af2cbf10deaf135f30d238e3e8a105dad" kindref="member">DepthIndex::Ranges::MAXIMUM_DEPTH_INDEX</ref>. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>If we call this API at least 1 time, we cannot set as <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DepthIndex_1a69e209901b5045f9943328fbb8989144a070fe29d5529300381f6c8a96ec8db49" kindref="member">DepthIndex::AUTO_INDEX</ref> after.</para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">index</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The depth index of this visual. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
